Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of St. John the Baptist, State of Louisiana (the "Parish") levy a special tax of seven (7) mills (the "Tax") on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $2,960,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the Tax for an entire year), for a period of thirty (30) years, beginning with the year 2017 and ending with the year 2046, for the purpose of paying any costs associated with constructing, acquiring, maintaining, operating, extending and/or improving levees, facilities and structures associated with outer flood protection systems within the Parish?
